description:
The static ENDPOINT_COUNTER (wallet/src/client.rs:35) enables round-robin load distribution across multiple lightwalletd endpoints in connect_with_failover(). However, the declaration has no comment explaining why it exists or what it does.

Without documentation, readers must examine the implementation to understand the purpose. Adding a line comment above the static explaining it's for round-robin endpoint rotation would make the code self-documenting and help maintainers understand the design intent.

Location: wallet/src/client.rs line 35
Current:
  static ENDPOINT_COUNTER: AtomicUsize = AtomicUsize::new(0);

Should have a preceding comment like:
  // Round-robin counter to distribute connections across multiple endpoints.
  // Used by connect_with_failover() to load-balance across DEFAULT_MAINNET_ENDPOINTS.
  static ENDPOINT_COUNTER: AtomicUsize = AtomicUsize::new(0);
